{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c4775cef-97dd-40d7-a9ba-add16d2732dd","content":"## 2. Configure NuGet.org Trusted Publisher\n\nOn **nuget.org**, register the trusted publisher **before** your first push:\n\n1. Go to **nuget.org → Manage Packages → Add Trusted Publisher** (or set it up during initial package registration)\n2. Fill in:\n   - **Repository owner:** `myorg`\n   - **Repository name:** `mylib`\n   - **Workflow filename:** `publish.yml`\n   - **Environment:** *(leave blank — no GH environment needed)*\n\n## How It Works\n\n- Pushing a tag like `v1.0.0` triggers the workflow.\n- `id-token: write` lets GitHub mint an OIDC token.\n- `dotnet nuget push` without `--api-key` automatically uses the OIDC token when NuGet.org recognizes the trusted publisher claim.\n- **No secrets or API keys needed** in your repo.\n\n## To publish\n\n```bash\ngit tag v1.0.0\ngit push origin v1.0.0\n```\n\nMake sure your `.csproj` has `<PackageId>`, `<Version>`, and other required package metadata. Want me to add those properties to the csproj?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f9438c5b-49e7-42b9-afc4-9eb65c8b5b19","outputTokens":283,"requestId":"0404:2C5A62:A1E50C:BC5076:69F3FB88"},"id":"810c2399-ded8-45c0-9221-798980732a27","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:02:08.480Z","parentId":"9b1d2abf-7398-4fc8-acd4-6a2ebc332426"}
